[3]
Date: Thu, 4 Sep 1997 15:29:09 -0400 (EDT)
From: Marjorie Anderson <marjorie@saturn.caps.maine.edu>
With the interest in prion diseases at an all time high, an older article
might stimulate some discussion.
Nature 1970 Sep 26;227(265):1341-1343. "Inactivation of the scrapie agent
by near monochromatic ultraviolet light." Latarjet R, Muel B, Haig DA,
Clarke MC, Alper T.
Perhaps the fear of CJD might be the catalyst that causes the public to
accept irradiation, if it can be proven effective against the agent that
causes BSE.
---
